%N A257239 Decimal expansion of the real root of x^3 + 4*x - 13.
%C A257239 This is related to the third of thirty problems posed by Niccolò Tartaglia to Antonio Maria Fiore in the year 1535 (in Venice it was still 1534). See the Katscher reference [in German] pp. 14, 15.
%C A257239 The problem is: find me a number which when added to 4 times its cube root gives 13. That is z + z^(1/3) = 13, or, with z = x^3, x^3 + 4*x = 13, with real solution x1. The solution to the problem is then z1 = x1^3 = 13 - 4*x1 (see the formula and example section).
%D A257239 Friedrich Katscher, Die Kubischen Gleichungen bei Nicolo Tartaglia, Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, 2001, Wien, Aufgabe XXV, pp. 13-16.
%H A257239 MacTutor History of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathshistory.st-andrews.ac.uk/Biographies/Tartaglia/">Niccolò Tartaglia</a>.
%H A257239 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_03">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 3</a>
%F A257239 The real solution x1 to x^3 + 4*x - 13 = 0 is
%F A257239 x1 = (1/6)*((1404 + 12*sqrt(14457))^(1/3) - (-1404 + 12*sqrt(14457))^(1/3)).
%F A257239 The two complex solutions are a + b*i and a - b*i, with a = -x1/2 and b = sqrt(3)*y1/2 where y1 = (1/6)*((1404+12*sqrt(14457))^(1/3) + (-1404 + 12*sqrt(14457))^(1/3)) with
%F A257239 y1 = 2.926590945638182088730632869966915335446... and
%F A257239 z1 = 5.809338022398154156043352227759054154638...
%e A257239 x1 = 1.797665494400461460989161943060236461340...
